<p>The <b>Chechen language</b> (Нохчийн мотт / Noxçiyꞑ mott; <a href="/wiki/Medieval" title="Medieval" class="mw-redirect">Medieval</a> Chechen: <span lang="fa" xml:lang="fa">نوًچین موت</span>) is spoken by more than 1.5 million people, mostly in <a href="/wiki/Chechnya" title="Chechnya">Chechnya</a> and by <a href="/wiki/Chechen_people" title="Chechen people">Chechen people</a> elsewhere. It is a member of the <a href="/wiki/Northeast_Caucasian_languages" title="Northeast Caucasian languages">Northeast Caucasian languages</a>.</p>
